gate: OPEN
task: S75-TE3
title: Verify and Fix Object Details Screen End-to-End
description: |
  Verify the complete object details flow works against old app feature parity.

  OLD APP OBJECT DETAILS FEATURES (iOS VehicleInfoModel + ContainerVC):
    Info panel (popup data from GET /ws/vehicledetails/:id):
      - Vehicle name
      - Ignition status (on/off)
      - Last date/time
      - Speed
      - Fuel level 1/2/3
      - Satellites count
      - Temperature sensor 1/2/3
      - Odometer
      - Address (reverse geocoded)

    History tab (GET /ws/track/daily/:id/:date):
      - Daily movement/stop log
      - Each entry: type (driving/parking), start time, end time, duration, distance
      - Mini-map snapshot showing the day's route
      - Date picker to navigate between days

    Events tab:
      - List of events for the selected object
      - Event type, time, description

  VERIFICATION CHECKLIST:
    1. Open Objects tab → tap a vehicle → ObjectDetailsScreen renders
    2. Info tab shows: ignition, speed, fuel1/2/3, satellites, temperature, odometer
       Data source: GET /ws/vehicledetails/:id
       Check null handling for fuel2/3, temperature (only fuel1 may be present)
    3. History tab:
       a. Loads daily track for today via GET /ws/track/daily/:id/:date
       b. Date format: YYYY-MM-DD — verify zero-padded (S74-TD3 fix)
       c. Driving entries show distance (non-null, .toFixed(1) safe)
       d. Parking entries show duration
       e. Mini-map renders and is stable (key = 'history-map-{vehicleId}', not lat-lon)
       f. Popup auto-opens on mount (useEffect with retry, not useLayoutEffect once)
       g. Previous date navigation works (changes displayed day)
    4. Events tab:
       a. Shows event list for the vehicle
       b. Event type labels are translated (use i18n keys)
    5. Back navigation returns to Objects list

  FIX ANY FAILURES found during verification.
  Pay special attention to the null-safety fix from sprint 63:
    (item.distance ?? 0).toFixed(1) — confirm still present and correct.

acceptance:
  - Object details opens and shows full vehicle info without errors
  - History tab shows driving/parking log with correct distance and duration
  - History mini-map renders stably (no destroy/recreate on data load)
  - Events tab shows event list
  - All numeric fields handle null/undefined safely
  - Back button returns to Objects list correctly

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
estimated: 2 hours
